    "encrypted": "false",
    "instructions_important": "false",
    "long_instructions": "#### Emotional Moments\r\n\r\n**Define:** Choose a song that moves through different emotional sections - maybe it starts calm and builds energy, or shifts from happy to dramatic. Your goal is to guide listeners through these emotional transitions using creative sequencing and instrument changes.\r\n\r\n**Prepare:** Pick a song and identify sounds that lead to a mood change. Think about how you'll use instruments and timing to support those shifts.\r\n\r\nIf you want to pick a new song, you can click the restart button in the upper-right corner [<i class=\"fa-solid fa-lightbulb\"></i> <i class=\"fa-solid fa-square-right\"></i>](#clickable=start-over-button)\r\n\r\n<div style=\"background:#ebe8f1; border: 0; border-radius: 10px; clear:both; padding: 5px\">\r\n\r\n**Musical Suggestions:**\r\n\r\n- *\"Hallelujah\" – Rosa Linn* (moody and atmospheric, with emotional peaks)\r\n- *\"Tightrope\" – Tinashe* (fluid groove with space to shape energy)\r\n- *\"In The Stars\" – Benson Boone* (nostalgic build-ups and emotional weight)\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n**Try:** Build at least three different musical sections, each representing a different emotion. Use effects or instrument changes to highlight the transitions. Sequence your code carefully so each emotional shift is clear and musically interesting.\r\n\r\n<div style=\"background:#ebe8f1; border: 0; border-radius: 10px; clear:both; padding: 5px\">\r\n\r\nNeed some help? Try the [<i class=\"fa-solid fa-book\"></i> Docs](#clickable=documentation-button) in the upper-right corner!\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n**Reflect:** Does your remix guide the listener through different emotions? Do the transitions feel natural and expressive? In order to complete this level, your remix must include:\r\n\r\n- At least 3 different beat tracks\r\n- At least 3 different bass tracks\r\n- At least 3 different lead tracks\r\n- At least 3 different musical sections with emotional shifts",
    "offer_browser_tts": "true",
